commit.message: remove legacy xf86misc, Gentoo Bug 720150 dropped x11-libs/libXxf86misc
mitigate SIGSEGV XFreeCursor from undef data.display
implicit declaration of function crypt

Fix getting the PAM file name

Fixes #12

Fix padding issue on some targets

GCC reports `offset of packed bit-field ‘green’ has changed in GCC 4.4`,
because there could be padding between uint8_t on some targets prior to
gcc 4.4 [1]. Switch to uint16_t so there will be no unintentional
padding.

[1] https://www.gnu.org/software/gcc/gcc-4.4/changes.html

Fixes #10

If possible, use Imlib2 for blurring

Using Imlib2 for blurring should significantly reduce computation time
comparing to the Gaussian convolution filter performed by the X server.

Fixes #9

Remap terminal ctrl-key sequence to valid X key

This commit adds remaps for ctrl-c, ctrl-h, ctrl-j and ctrl-m
respectively as escape, backspace, enter and enter.

Fixes #8

Allow KP Enter to confirm input

Fixes #6

Customize build-in default PAM service

It seems, that there is no sane default for build-in PAM service. In
order to simplify package maintenance for different Linux distributions,
this commit allows specifying default PAM service by the package
maintainer.

Note, that this commit makes non-backward compatible change. The PAM
"module" is renamed to PAM "service", which is consistent with the PAM
documentation.

Fixes #5

Added PAM module option

Select the pam.d/* module to authenticate against via the command line
option pam:module=*, which defaults to "system-auth".

Fixes #4

Link with -lrt if necessary

For glibc versions before 2.17 the rt library is required.

Check for NULL pointer

Creating XRM database from the NULL pointer is not the best idea there. It
has turned out, that the Xlib function does not have any protection against
coding sloppiness...

Fixes #3
Fix segmentation fault upon image module free

Reparent input window

Placing input window as a standalone one makes our locker a multi-window
application. Such a configuration is badly (though correct) interpreted
by compositor manager (compton) which could unredirect all windows when
opaque full-screen window is detected. By reparenting input window with
the background window (if applicable) we are postponing compositor action
until screen is unlocked - fix unnecessary screen flickering.
Use POSIX spawn instead of fork/exec

Fix for grayscale conversion

The grayscale conversion depends on the depth of the image and the image
depth - in our case - depends on the depth of the screen. In most cases,
screen depth is set to 24 bits, however this assumption leads to weird
glitches...

The new code has explicit branches for different types of depths. Also the
conversion is done according to the colorimetric strategy - the grayscale
image is more GIMP-like.
Optimization for X Render Extension check

Check for read errors

Mitigate theoretical segmentation fault.

Use pkg-config for library check

X Ext and X Misc provide pkg-config configuration file. This way of setting
up the dependencies makes the check consistent with the rest of libraries.

Fixes #2

Configuration script clean-up

Xf86misc component of the X11 library requires special attention. The header
file is not self-contained, it requires extra header files (the Xlib itself)
to be included beforehand, otherwise compilation may fail...

Fixes #2
Fix typo in the license header

Use preprocessor for Linux-specific clock option

Boot-time clock is available on the Linux systems only. If this clock type
is not available, provide sane fall-back - monotonic clock.
Documentation update
Cosmetic changes

Do not generate dummy window

Use background window as a desktop cover only and read all events from
the screen's root window. This small change saves for us lots of bytes
of code, which are priceless.

Use provided string length

String returned by the X string lookup function is not NULL terminated!

Do not cache internal Xlib data

It has turned out (actually I have found out), that all structures related
to the Xlib display handler can be obtained via Xlib display macros. This
knowledge has leaded to the optimization of our internal data structures -
lower memory footprint and improved code maintainability (less code).

Fix include order

Make sure, that our base include file is included prior to other files.
This include ordering might help finding bugs in the future.
Fix structure member reference
Blank cursor module - hide cursor pointer
